                                            A bad first impression, but I get it now.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>This year marked Google Photos' 10th birthday, and to celebrate, a redesign was announced. The most noticeable changes appeared in the editor, and after initially being very against this change, it's really grown on me over time. </p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 23 Sep 2025 14:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/i-thought-google-photos-ruined-the-editor-but-it-won-me-over/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Is It Safe to Keep a Portable Battery in a Hot Car?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/is-it-safe-to-keep-a-portable-battery-in-a-hot-car/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/portable-battery-overheating-on-a-car-dashboard-with-warning-icon-and-smoke.png" length="2442" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[battery]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mobile Accessories]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            You probably should think twice about leaving that battery there.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>People leave portable batteries in their cars for emergencies or to recharge their phones on the go. After all, a car seems like the perfect mobile storage unit, ready to shuttle our gadgets wherever we need them. However, this is a huge mistake that can cost you a lot of money.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 23 Sep 2025 13:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/is-it-safe-to-keep-a-portable-battery-in-a-hot-car/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Your Google TV Just Got a Lot Smarter]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-google-tv-just-got-a-lot-smarter/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/52766779525_5d1d85812b_o-1.jpg" length="192" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Smart Home]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google TV]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Google Assistant is dead.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>As generative AI rises and becomes commonplace in our lives, old-school voice assistants such as Google Assistant are the ones getting the boot. We've seen a widespread effort by Google to <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/gemini-replace-google-assistant-2025/" target="_blank">replace Assistant with Gemini</a>—even as Gemini isn't quite yet capable of doing everything Assistant can, but that's an issue for another day. Now, your TV is next in that big step.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 23 Sep 2025 13:23:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/your-google-tv-just-got-a-lot-smarter/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How to Enable Hardware-Accelerated GPU Scheduling in Windows 10 and 11]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/756935/how-to-enable-hardware-accelerated-gpu-scheduling-in-windows-11/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mahesh Makvana]]></dc:creator><dc:creator><![CDATA[Samir Makwana]]></dc:creator><dc:creator><![CDATA[Nick Lewis]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/a-gpu-with-an-activated-switch.jpg" length="259" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 11]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 10]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Optimization]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Want to make your apps and games a bit smoother? Try this.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Windows 10 and Windows 11 come with an advanced setting, called Hardware-Accelerated GPU Scheduling, which can <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/353730/how-to-view-and-improve-your-games-frame-per-second-fps/" target="_blank">boost gaming</a> and video performance using your PC's GPU. We'll show you how to enable the feature, potentially get a performance increase, and ensure some of the best features available on modern GPUs work like they should.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 23 Sep 2025 13:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/756935/how-to-enable-hardware-accelerated-gpu-scheduling-in-windows-11/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google Is Hoping to Fix Its Biggest Play Store Problem]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/google-is-hoping-to-fix-its-biggest-play-store-problem/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Joe Fedewa]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/google-play-hero.jpg" length="139" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Play Store]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            And some welcomed changes to Google Play Games.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Considering it's owned by a company known for search, it’s <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/google-play-store-big-problem/" target="_blank">notoriously difficult</a> to find stuff in the Google Play Store. Google is rolling out a few changes that might make the whole experience a lot less painful.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 23 Sep 2025 13:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/google-is-hoping-to-fix-its-biggest-play-store-problem/</guid></item></channel>
